## KEY MILESTONE DATES

### April-June 2025
- **April 10**: Queen's Share spirit run begins
- **April 16**: First molasses fermentation begins (M001)
- **April 24**: Queen's Share barrel fill
- **April 28**: First stripping run begins
- **May 12**: First regular spirit run begins (SR001)
- **May 19**: First barrel fill
- **May 25**: Order molasses
- **June 24**: Second barrel fill

### July-September 2025 
- **July 24**: Third barrel fill
- **July 25**: Molasses delivery
- **September 1**: Fourth barrel fill

### October-December 2025
- **October 6**: Fifth barrel fill
- **October 13-16**: Sugarcane harvest
- **October 17-22**: Fresh cane juice fermentation (C001)
- **October 27-31**: Cane juice stripping
- **December 2**: Sixth barrel fill (molasses)
- **December 10-14**: Cane spirit run (CSR001)
- **December 16**: Cane barrel fill
- **December 19-January 2**: Holiday break - No production

## HANDOVER PROCESS

### Daily Handover (11:00 AM - 2:00 PM)
1. Kernean (4:00 AM - 2:00 PM) provides detailed handover to Frank (11:00 AM - 9:00 PM)
2. 3-hour overlap ensures thorough knowledge transfer on:
   - Current distillation parameters
   - Fermentation status
   - Collection vessel details
   - Cut points for spirit runs
   - Quality measurements
   - Next day preparation requirements

### Special Handover Notes
- Wednesdays: Kernean off (comp day), Frank handles full distillation day
- Fridays: Kernean only, no handover required
- Saturdays: Kernean when scheduled, otherwise off
- Sundays: Jovan handles all operations

### Compensation Day Protocol
When Kernean is off (typically Wednesdays):
- Frank receives detailed written instructions from previous day
- Production activities scheduled for lower complexity
- Frank handles complete distillation cycle
